Officials say the suspect tried to bribe the investigating officer to have his case thrown out of court. JOHANNESBURG A South African National Defence Force(SANDF) member has been arrested for allegedly sexually harassing a patient at the 68 Air School sickbay in Pretoria. The suspect has been removed from the school while investigations are underway. Officials say the SANDF employee tried to bribe the investigating officer to have his case thrown out of court. The Defence Ministrys Ronald Maseko says, The police, the South African Police Service and the Military Police co-operated and that eventually led to him being arrested. He is currently being held at the Lyttleton police station pending the outcome of his court appearance today.